nally is not n=\r\needed. I would say that we are very much observing Brahmacharya. Now coming=\r\n to Ojas I doubt that Ojas can be so physical as Semen. If the act of Sex i=\r\ns itself perfomed as an offering to God and without any thoughts other than=\r\n that of God then where is the question of loosing any spiritual energy . I=\r\nn fact you are adding to your spiritual growth. \nI have observed a change i=\r\nn myself after doing this practically over the past couple of months. I hav=\r\ne found that gradually over a period of time even though its possible to co=\r\nmpletely abstain from physical sex, it is also possible to avoid getting sw=\r\nayed by it and also not crave for it.\n=C2=A0\nContinuing further=C2=A0, how =\r\nwould one justify &quot;Nightfalls&quot; which is a natural phenomenon wherein the bo=\r\ndy automatically purges excess semen collected over a period of time when o=\r\nne is asleep without the persons control.In other words it is an involuntar=\r\ny=C2=A0action just like breathing.\n=C2=A0\nCan this also be=C2=A0intrepreted=\r\n as break in Brahmacharya? I would be keen to know the experiences of those=\r\n persons who have abstained from physical sex for an extended period of tim=\r\ne and=C2=A0what they think=C2=A0of=C2=A0&quot;Nightfalls&quot; .\n=C2=A0\n************ =\r\n********* ********* ********* ********* ********* ********* ********* *****=\r\n**** ********* ********* ********* ********* ********\n=C2=A0\nI think that e=\r\nvery action that we do should be done with the thought of an offering to go=\r\nd. For example even while having food , we can think each bite as an offeri=\r\nng to Ganapathi in fire (actually there is a fire in our stomach which burn=\r\ns the food) , Our entire body can be visuilased like a living moving Homa k=\r\nundam where we continuously offer ahuti of differnet materials. If we conci=\r\nously make this effort over a period of time we would think less about the =\r\nprocess of eating=C2=A0food itself , the accompanying pleasure of taste etc=\r\n and concentrate more on mental homam which we are performing. Every though=\r\nt process can be considered as an ahuti inside the mental fire in our soul.=\r\nLike this every action that we do in our daily life can be thought as a hom=\r\nam itself and thereby achieve the state of mind where there is no distincti=\r\non between the so called &quot;Pure&quot; and &quot;Impure&quot; , &quot;Good&quot; and &quot;Bad&quot; and so on.\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nPlease let us=C2=A0know your thoughts on this. If possible try to ge=\r\nt Manishji&#39;s opinion on this as well.\n=C2=A0\nThanks and Regards,\nGirish Sun=\r\ndaram\n\n\n\n\n\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@charter. net&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@ yah=\r\noogroups. com\nSent: Wed, March 3, 2010 5:03:20 AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] B=\r\nrahmacharya (Re: Regarding Ganapati Homam...)\n\n\n=C2=A0 \n\nNamaste Biswajit,\n=\r\n\nGood luck with homam. Others answered your questions and I will leave them=\r\n. But I want to say a few words on (3) as the recent discussion on aghora s=\r\neems to have created some confusion. It is very easy to misunderstand when =\r\nwe are communicating verbally, because one&#39;s own mental conditioning has a =\r\nrole in deciding how one interprets words, sentences and their sub-text. It=\r\n is more so when we are talking about delicate matters.\n\n* * *\n\n&gt; 3. When t=\r\nhe talking of &quot;AGHORA&quot; going on, is it really needed\n&gt; to perform &quot;Bramhach=\r\nariya&quot; for daily ganapati homam?\n\nBrahmacharya is very important in any spi=\r\nritual sadhana. Period. As Narayan said, sexual activity results in loss of=\r\n ojas (subtle vitality) and wastes a part of one&#39;s creative essence. Doing =\r\nsadhana without brahmacharya is like filling a water pot that is leaking th=\r\nrough a hole. Even if you succeed in filling the pot with water, it will so=\r\non become\n empty!\n\nJust as a filled water pot that is leaking may still sat=\r\nisfy the thirst of someone who takes a glass of water from it, similarly a =\r\nperson doing sadhana without brahmacharya may sometimes be able to do his d=\r\nharma and serve his purpose in the world. So, it is a good idea to do sadha=\r\nna even as one&#39;s brahmacharya is not good yet. But, the best will be if the=\r\n filled water pot is not leaking and holds all the water. Similarly, a sadh=\r\naka who is accumulating some shakti through sadhana and does not leak that =\r\nenergy through acts of lust, anger, greed, jealosy etc will be able to serv=\r\ne dharma better.\n\nIf there are 12 people who maintain physical and mental b=\r\nrahmacharya for a few years while doing homam everyday, I think the world c=\r\nan be changed.\n\n* * *\n\nIf an aghora sits naked with partner and chants mant=\r\nra, please remember that the goal isn&#39;t having sex. This practice is by mea=\r\nns a glorification of sex. The goal is to *resist*.\n Even if the mind is ov=\r\nerwhelmed in the beginning with thrill and one ends up having sex, the goal=\r\n is to reach a stage where mind is not looking at nakedness or intimacy as =\r\nsomething to be excited about. The goal is to reach a stage where brahmacha=\r\nrya can be maintained despite such provocation.\n\nIn fact, the true meaning =\r\nof brahmacharya is not only to refrain from physical sex but also to refrai=\r\nn from sexual thoughts in the mind. Many married people of today may be abl=\r\ne to set time limits (e.g. 40 days, 100 days, 1 year etc) and maintain phys=\r\nical brahmacharya for that time, but it may be difficult to refrain from me=\r\nntal thoughts.\n\nAn aghora tries to incinerate the root cause of those thoug=\r\nhts in his mind (what Manish called as &quot;sampradaaha&quot; ). Mind considers some=\r\n things as pure and some things as impure. The &quot;impure&quot; objects and circums=\r\ntances are considered impure because they cause thrill or some other distur=\r\nbance to the mind and waver it\n from god. But an aghora puts them right in =\r\nthe middle of a &quot;pure&quot; activity (e.g. meditation), forcing oneself to deal =\r\nwith them. After some time, the impure objects do not cause any thrill or o=\r\nther disturbance to waver the mind from god. Then they are no longer impure=\r\n! For example, what is impure about a naked body? The only thing impure abo=\r\nut it is that it arouses certain thoughts in mind that disturb the mind and=\r\n waver it from god. If a naked body no longer arouses such thoughts, what i=\r\ns impure about it?\n\nThat is the basic thinking in this practice. Some yogis=\r\n may physically abstain from sex and even stay away from exposure to opposi=\r\nte sex, for several decades. But, if such a person is placed in front of a =\r\nnaked beauty, what thoughts will go on his mind? For all you know, his mind=\r\n may indeed be disturbed and waver from god. An aghora tries to incinerate =\r\nthe very notion in the mind that so and so thing is something to be aroused=\r\n by, not by\n staying away from it but by being with it and yet trying to fo=\r\ncus the mind on god.\n\nBottomline: An aghora engaging in this practice may s=\r\ntray from brahmacharya in the beginning, but the goal is to attain more per=\r\nfect brahmacharya later on. The goal of this practice is to attain brahmach=\r\narya.\n\nIf one does not keep brahmacharya in the beginning of sadhana, it ma=\r\ny be ok. But, to really start progressing, one needs to somehow or the othe=\r\nr attain some level of brahmacharya and keep perfecting it.\n\n* * *\n\nThe coa=\r\nrse meaning of brahmacharya is physical celibacy.\n\nThe finer meaning of bra=\r\nhmacharya is physical celibacy and refraining from any sexual thoughts even=\r\n in the mind.\n\nThe finest meaning of brahmacharya is refraining from lust, =\r\nanger, greed, delusion, wantonness and jealosy and establishing mind in Bra=\r\nhman always. Brahmacharya literally means &quot;engaging in Brahman or Self&quot;. On=\r\ne experiences lust, anger, greed, jealosy\n etc only when one&#39;s mind perceiv=\r\nes and engages with impermanent manifestations of Self (e.g. a beautiful la=\r\ndy, a bad person, a lot of money, a person being appreciated more than me e=\r\ntc) and NOT when one&#39;s mind engages in true Self. Thus the truest brahmacha=\r\nrya comes only on Self-realization. But one can start with physical celibac=\r\ny and control over anger.\n\nRome is not built in a day.\n\nBottomline: It is v=\r\nery important to keep brahmacharya, even using the coarse meaning above. St=\r\nart off with some level of brahmacharya and try to improve it as time goes =\r\non. Never be frustrated with lack of progress and keep trying.\n\n* * *\n\nBTW,=\r\n regarding (4), even after fire goes away, you can meditate. Fire will be b=\r\nurning in the ember form for a long time. So Agni is still there consuming =\r\nyour offerings, even after it seems like there is no fire.\n\nKeep it as chea=\r\np as you can, based on your financial level. Little ghee, fallen wood stick=\r\ns\n collected manually and some sesame seeds may be all you need.\n\nBest rega=\r\nrds,\nNarasimha\n------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- -------=\r\n-- -\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It =\r\nYourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\nhttp://www.Vedi=\r\ncAst rologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFil ms.org\nS=\r\npirituality: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/vedic- wisdom\nJyotish writings=\r\n: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/JyotishWri tings\n------------ --------- -=\r\n-------- --------- --------- --------- -\n\n---- biswa108 &lt;biswa1975@yahoo. c=\r\nom&gt; wrote: \n&gt; NAMASKAR to all\n&gt; \n&gt; I have been performing Ganapati Homama f=\r\nor the last three weeks, credit goes to all of my seniors/members and Gurus=\r\n of this beautiful forum...\n&gt; \n&gt; Now I need some practical approach best su=\r\nitable for me