on this as well.&lt;/div&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Thanks and Regards,&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Girish Sundaram&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:12pt;FONT-FAMILY:times new roman, new yo=\r\nrk, times, serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:12pt;BORDER-LEFT:#1010ff 2p=\r\nx solid;FONT-FAMILY:times new roman, new york, times, serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=3D=\r\n&quot;Tahoma&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n&lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;F=\r\nrom:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@charter. net&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span styl=\r\ne=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic-wisdom@ yahoogroups. com&lt;br&gt;&lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Wed, March 3, 2010 5:03=\r\n:20 AM&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;Subject:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; [vedic-w=\r\nisdom] Brahmacharya (Re: Regarding Ganapati Homam...)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;span&gt;=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt; \n&lt;div id=3D&quot;ygrp-text&quot;&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Namaste Biswajit,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Good luck=\r\n with homam. Others answered your questions and I will leave them. But I wa=\r\nnt to say a few words on (3) as the recent discussion on aghora seems to ha=\r\nve created some confusion. It is very easy to misunderstand when we are com=\r\nmunicating verbally, because one&#39;s own mental conditioning has a role in de=\r\nciding how one interprets words, sentences and their sub-text. It is more s=\r\no when we are talking about delicate matters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* * *&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; 3. W=\r\nhen the talking of &quot;AGHORA&quot; going on, is it really needed&lt;br&gt;&gt; to perfor=\r\nm &quot;Bramhachariya&quot; for daily ganapati homam?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Brahmacharya is very imp=\r\nortant in any spiritual sadhana. Period. As Narayan said, sexual activity r=\r\nesults in loss of ojas (subtle vitality) and wastes a part of one&#39;s creativ=\r\ne essence. Doing sadhana without brahmacharya is like filling a water pot t=\r\nhat is leaking through a hole. Even if you succeed in filling the pot with =\r\nwater, it will soon become\n empty!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Just as a filled water pot that i=\r\ns leaking may still satisfy the thirst of someone who takes a glass of wate=\r\nr from it, similarly a person doing sadhana without brahmacharya may someti=\r\nmes be able to do his dharma and serve his purpose in the world. So, it is =\r\na good idea to do sadhana even as one&#39;s brahmacharya is not good yet. But, =\r\nthe best will be if the filled water pot is not leaking and holds all the w=\r\nater. Similarly, a sadhaka who is accumulating some shakti through sadhana =\r\nand does not leak that energy through acts of lust, anger, greed, jealosy e=\r\ntc will be able to serve dharma better.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If there are 12 people who m=\r\naintain physical and mental brahmacharya for a few years while doing homam =\r\neveryday, I think the world can be changed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* * *&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If an aghor=\r\na sits naked with partner and chants mantra, please remember that the goal =\r\nisn&#39;t having sex. This practice is by means a glorification of sex. The goa=\r\nl is to *resist*.\n Even if the mind is overwhelmed in the beginning with th=\r\nrill and one ends up having sex, the goal is to reach a stage where mind is=\r\n not looking at nakedness or intimacy as something to be excited about. The=\r\n goal is to reach a stage where brahmacharya can be maintained despite such=\r\n provocation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In fact, the true meaning of brahmacharya is not only =\r\nto refrain from physical sex but also to refrain from sexual thoughts in th=\r\ne mind. Many married people of today may be able to set time limits (e.g. 4=\r\n0 days, 100 days, 1 year etc) and maintain physical brahmacharya for that t=\r\nime, but it may be difficult to refrain from mental thoughts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;An agh=\r\nora tries to incinerate the root cause of those thoughts in his mind (what =\r\nManish called as &quot;sampradaaha&quot; ). Mind considers some things as pure and so=\r\nme things as impure. The &quot;impure&quot; objects and circumstances are considered =\r\nimpure because they cause thrill or some other disturbance to the mind and =\r\nwaver it\n from god. But an aghora puts them right in the middle of a &quot;pure&quot;=\r\n activity (e.g. meditation), forcing oneself to deal with them. After some =\r\ntime, the impure objects do not cause any thrill or other disturbance to wa=\r\nver the mind from god. Then they are no longer impure! For example, what is=\r\n impure about a naked body? The only thing impure about it is that it arous=\r\nes certain thoughts in mind that disturb the mind and waver it from god. If=\r\n a naked body no longer arouses such thoughts, what is impure about it?&lt;br&gt;=\r\n&lt;br&gt;That is the basic thinking in this practice. Some yogis may physically =\r\nabstain from sex and even stay away from exposure to opposite sex, for seve=\r\nral decades. But, if such a person is placed in front of a naked beauty, wh=\r\nat thoughts will go on his mind? For all you know, his mind may indeed be d=\r\nisturbed and waver from god. An aghora tries to incinerate the very notion =\r\nin the mind that so and so thing is something to be aroused by, not by\n sta=\r\nying away from it but by being with it and yet trying to focus the mind on =\r\ngod.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bottomline: An aghora engaging in this practice may stray from =\r\nbrahmacharya in the beginning, but the goal is to attain more perfect brahm=\r\nacharya later on. The goal of this practice is to attain brahmacharya.&lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;If one does not keep brahmacharya in the beginning of sadhana, it may be=\r\n ok. But, to really start progressing, one needs to somehow or the other at=\r\ntain some level of brahmacharya and keep perfecting it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* * *&lt;br&gt;&lt;br=\r\n&gt;The coarse meaning of brahmacharya is physical celibacy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The finer =\r\nmeaning of brahmacharya is physical celibacy and refraining from any sexual=\r\n thoughts even in the mind.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The finest meaning of brahmacharya is re=\r\nfraining from lust, anger, greed, delusion, wantonness and jealosy and esta=\r\nblishing mind in Brahman always. Brahmacharya literally means &quot;engaging in =\r\nBrahman or Self&quot;. One experiences lust, anger, greed, jealosy\n etc only whe=\r\nn one&#39;s mind perceives and engages with impermanent manifestations of Self =\r\n(e.g. a beautiful lady, a bad person, a lot of money, a person being apprec=\r\niated more than me etc) and NOT when one&#39;s mind engages in true Self. Thus =\r\nthe truest brahmacharya comes only on Self-realization. But one can start w=\r\nith physical celibacy and control over anger.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Rome is not built in a=\r\n day.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bottomline: It is very important to keep brahmacharya, even us=\r\ning the coarse meaning above. Start off with some level of brahmacharya and=\r\n try to improve it as time goes on. Never be frustrated with lack of progre=\r\nss and keep trying.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* * *&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;BTW, regarding (4), even after fire=\r\n goes away, you can meditate. Fire will be burning in the ember form for a =\r\nlong time. So Agni is still there consuming your offerings, even after it s=\r\neems like there is no fire.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Keep it as cheap as you can, based on yo=\r\nur financial level. Little ghee, fallen wood sticks\n collected manually and=\r\n some sesame seeds may be all you need.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- --------- -&lt;br&gt;Free =\r\nJyotish Software, Free Jyotish L